## ðŸ“‹ Overview

A machine learning application that detects whether text is **AI-generated** or **human-written** using stylometric analysis and lexical features. It also includes a **text humanization module** to transform AI-generated content into more natural-sounding text.

## âœ¨ Features

- **AI vs Human Detection**: Analyzes text using TF-IDF vectorization and stylometric features
- **Confidence Scoring**: Provides prediction confidence percentage
- **Text Humanization**: Rewrites AI-generated text to sound more natural
- **Writing Style Analysis**: Extracts 6+ stylometric features
- **User-Friendly Interface**: Built with Streamlit

## ðŸ”§ Technical Stack

- **Machine Learning**: scikit-learn
- **Text Vectorization**: TF-IDF
- **UI Framework**: Streamlit
- **Model Serialization**: joblib

## ðŸ“Š Stylometric Features

The detector analyzes:
- Word count & sentence count
- Average word length
- Lexical diversity
- Punctuation frequency
- Character case distribution
